completion.item: <[!CDATA[The MessageBox style constant for an ABORT button; the only valid combination is ABORT|RETRY|IGNORE (value is 1<<9).]]>
<[!CDATA[Style constant for application modal behavior (value is 1<<16).]]>
<[!CDATA[Style constant for align bottom behavior (value is 1<<10, since align DOWN and align BOTTOM are considered the same).]]>
<[!CDATA[The MessageBox style constant for a CANCEL button, valid combinations are OK|CANCEL, YES|NO|CANCEL, RETRY|CANCEL (value is 1<<8).]]>
<[!CDATA[Style constant for close box trim (value is 1<<6, since we do not distinguish between CLOSE style and MENU style).]]>

<[!CDATA[Indicates that a default should be used (value is 0).
NOTE: In SWT, this value is -1, but that causes problems with bitwise JavaScript operators...]]>
<[!CDATA[Style constant for align down behavior (value is 1<<10, since align DOWN and align BOTTOM are considered the same).]]>
<[!CDATA[Indicates that a user-interface component is being dragged, for example dragging the thumb of a scroll bar (value is 1).]]>
<[!CDATA[Style constant for full row selection behavior (value is 1<<16).]]>
<[!CDATA[The MessageBox style constant for an IGNORE button, the only valid combination is ABORT|RETRY|IGNORE (value is 1<<11).]]>
<[!CDATA[Style constant for shell menu trim (value is 1<<6, since we do not distinguish between CLOSE style and MENU style).]]>
<[!CDATA[Style constant for multi-selection behavior in lists and multiple line support on text fields (value is 1<<1).]]>
<[!CDATA[The MessageBox style constant for NO button, valid combinations are YES|NO, YES|NO|CANCEL (value is 1<<7).]]>
<[!CDATA[The MessageBox style constant for an OK button, valid combinations are OK, OK|CANCEL (value is 1<<5).]]>
<[!CDATA[The MessageBox style constant for a RETRY button, valid combinations are ABORT|RETRY|IGNORE, RETRY|CANCEL (value is 1<<10).]]>
<[!CDATA[Style constant for single selection behavior in lists and single line support on text fields (value is 1<<2).]]>
<[!CDATA[Style constant for system modal behavior (value is 1<<17).]]>
<[!CDATA[Style constant for align top behavior (value is 1<<7, since align UP and align TOP are considered the same).]]>
<[!CDATA[Style constant for align up behavior (value is 1<<7, since align UP and align TOP are considered the same).]]>
<[!CDATA[The MessageBox style constant for YES button, valid combinations are YES|NO, YES|NO|CANCEL (value is 1<<6).]]>
